Package nl.pim16aap2.bigdoors.doors

Interface IDoor

All Known Subinterfaces:
IPerpetualMover
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractDoor, BigDoor, Clock, DoorBase, Drawbridge, Elevator, Flag, GarageDoor, Portcullis, RevolvingDoor, SlidingDoor, Windmill
public interface IDoor
Represents a door. Every implementation of this interface should be an DoorBase.
Author:
Pim

    • isDoorOwner

      boolean isDoorOwner(UUID player)
      Checks if a player with a given UUID is a (co-)owner of this door with any level of ownership.

      If the level of ownership matters, use getDoorOwner(UUID) instead.

      Parameters:
      player - The UUID of a player.
      Returns:
      True if the player with the given UUID is an owner of this door with any level of ownership.

    • isDoorOwner

    • getOpenDir

      RotateDirection getOpenDir()
      Gets the RotateDirection this IDoor will open if currently closed.

      Note that if it's currently in the open status, it is supposed go in the opposite direction, as the closing direction is the opposite of the opening direction. This isn't taken into account by this method.

      Returns:
      The RotateDirection this IDoor will open in.

    • setOpenDir

      void setOpenDir(RotateDirection rotateDirection)
      Sets the RotateDirection this IDoor will open if currently closed.

      Note that if it's currently in the open status, it is supposed go in the opposite direction, as the closing direction is the opposite of the opening direction.

      Parameters:
      rotateDirection - The RotateDirection this IDoor will open in.

    • getBlockCount

      int getBlockCount()
      Retrieve the total number of blocks this IDoor is made out of. If invalidated or not calculated * yet, it is (re)calculated first.

      It's calculated once and then stored until invalidated.

      Returns:
      Total number of blocks this IDoor is made out of.

    • getDimensions

      Vector3Di getDimensions()
      Gets the dimensions of this door.

      If a door has a min and max X value of 120, for example, it would have a X-dimension of 0. If the min X value is 119 instead, it would have an X-dimension of 1.

      Returns:
      The dimensions of this door.

    • getChunkId

      long getChunkId()
      Returns:
      The simple hash of the chunk in which the power block resides.
